  &lt;body face=&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;&gt;
    The law of conservation of momentum is a fundamental law of nature, which 
    states that the total momentum of a closed system of objects (which has no 
    interactions with external agents) is constant. One of the consequences of 
    this is that the centre of mass of any system of objects will always 
    continue with the same velocity unless acted on by a force outside the 
    system. The simulation on the right shows that swinging a pendulum hung on 
    a cart cannot cause the whole system to move along horizontally.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Note 
    that this simulation shows the bending effect of the cantilever beam and 
    the supporting post.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;input value=&quot;Run&quot; name=&quot;button name&quot; selfscript=&quot;enablecomponent 0 false;enablecomponent 1 true;&quot; script=&quot;script:mw2d:1:run;&quot; alt=&quot;tooltip&quot; type=&quot;submit&quot;&gt;&lt;input name=&quot;button name&quot; value=&quot;Stop&quot; selfscript=&quot;enablecomponent 0 true;enablecomponent 1 false;&quot; script=&quot;script:mw2d:1:stop;&quot; alt=&quot;tooltip&quot; type=&quot;submit&quot;&gt;&lt;input name=&quot;button name&quot; value=&quot;Reset&quot; selfscript=&quot;enablecomponent 0 true;enablecomponent 1 false;&quot; script=&quot;script:mw2d:1:reset;&quot; alt=&quot;tooltip&quot; type=&quot;submit&quot;&gt;
